cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it proposes a new approach to model initialization and compares the performance of the proposed model set to previous stable RNNs and vanilla RNNs. It also discusses the trade-off between stability and expressibility in recurrent models, which is a common topic in machine learning research. 

It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with recurrent neural networks and proposes a new method for training them. 

The paper's focus on stability analysis of non-linear systems suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). 

The use of recurrent neural networks in various applications, such as natural language processing and image captioning, suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
